{"cursor":"5406","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nInformation Systems are more and more developed in and for the global market.\nThis field can be seen as a research discipline in the Information systems\ndomain but has a variety of specific challenges. Damian, D., Moitra, D.,\nâGuest Editors' Introduction: Global Software Development: How far Have We\nCome?,â IEEE Software,23(5), 17-19, 2006 Typical questions regard\n* How to design information systems for a global market. Should there be\n  standardized or localized products and services? Prikladnicki, R., Audy,\n  J. L. N., Damian, D., Oliveira, T. C., âDistributed Software Development:\n  Practices and challenges indifferent business strategies of offshoring and\n  onshoring,â Intâl Conf on Global Software Engineering, 262-274, Germany,\n  2007\n* How to organize the distributed work processes when working in different\n  locations?\n* How to adapt / localize specific components of systems, such as adapting the\n  user interfaces? Marcus, A., & Gould, E. W. (2000). Crosscurrents:\n  Cultural dimensions and global web user-interface design. Interactions, 7(4),\n  32â46.\n* Which factors (such as national culture) influence development / adaptation /\n  deployment processes? Leidner D, Kayworth T (2006) A Review of Culture in\n  Information Systems Research: Toward a Theory of Infor-mation Technology\n  Culture Conflict. MISQ, 30(2), S 357-399.\n* How to enable efficient communication and collaboration? These questions are\n  not complete but show some key issues for the field in research and practice.\n","linknr":134,"url":"Global_Information_Systems","recorded":1374783912,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Global_information_system&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Global_information_system&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special